cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of finite-state models in software engineering, specifically in control systems development. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Boolean satisfiability problem (SAT) and counterexample-guided synthesis in inferring finite-state models. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with the development of function blocks (FBs) defined by the IEC 61499 international standard for distributed automation systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an automatic approach for inferring finite-state models from behavior examples and temporal properties. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper focuses on the development of finite-state models in control systems.
